# Data Quality Review

Use this prompt to review data quality practices, validation rules, and monitoring for data pipelines and datasets.

---

## Data Quality Review for [DATASET_OR_PIPELINE]

### Phase 1: Completeness

- [ ] All expected records are present (row count validation)
- [ ] No missing values in required fields
- [ ] All expected time periods are covered (no gaps)
- [ ] All expected entities are present (no missing partitions)

| Field | Null Rate Target | Actual | Pass? |
|-------|-----------------|--------|-------|
| | < X% | | |

---

### Phase 2: Accuracy

- [ ] Values are within expected domains (enums, ranges)
- [ ] Cross-field consistency checks pass (e.g., start_date <= end_date)
- [ ] Aggregations match source totals (reconciliation)
- [ ] Spot-check samples against source of truth

| Validation Rule | Expected | Actual | Pass? |
|-----------------|----------|--------|-------|
| | | | |

---

### Phase 3: Consistency

- [ ] Same entity has consistent attributes across tables
- [ ] Timestamps use consistent timezone (UTC preferred)
- [ ] Units are consistent (currency, measurement)
- [ ] Naming conventions are followed

---

### Phase 4: Timeliness

| Dataset | Freshness SLA | Current Freshness | Pass? |
|---------|---------------|-------------------|-------|
| | | | |

- [ ] Data arrives within SLA
- [ ] Staleness is detected and alerted
- [ ] Late data handling strategy is defined

---

### Phase 5: Data Contracts

- [ ] Schema is versioned and documented
- [ ] Breaking changes follow migration procedures
- [ ] Downstream consumers are notified of changes
- [ ] Contract tests exist between producer and consumer

---

